Previous Save Backup¶{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Calibri;}{\f1\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}{&1310}{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}{&1310}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\lang9\f0\fs22 Business degrees are the most popular college degree for a reason - people with business degrees earn roughly 16% more than the median salary of those with other degrees.  But the true draw of a business degree is flexibility.  The swiss army knife of college degrees, they lay the groundwork to literally hundreds of different jobs, in a variety of different fields.  Here’s just a small sampling of what you could end up doing:{&1310}\par Sales:{&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl0\slmult1 The starting point for a lot of graduates, sales work is a great way to get your foot in the door of your industry of choice.  Since all types of companies need salespeople, you have almost limitless options when it comes to the field, whether that’s technology, medical, green energy, or many others.  Though a business degree isn’t essential to getting a sales job, it will help you with advancement - people who have the skills and the degree are more likely to snag promotions and new opportunities.  {&1310}\par Marketing:{&1310}\par Marketing covers a wide variety of jobs and talents, and in itself can be a career path.  Like sales, marketing is a flexible and scalable line of work, that continues to shift and evolve with changes in the industry.  Much marketing efforts today are shifting towards online and new media, and working as a marketing director will allow you to explore these emerging trends and learn what motivates people's buying decisions, a core compenent of any profitable company.  {&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Management{&47}Administration:{&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl0\slmult1 If organizing and planning is your thing, you might be well suited as a manager or administrator.  They guide the day to day of business, as well as strategize to solve big-picture problems of companies both large and small.  Every company’s needs are different, but many business administrators lead teams and rely on good communication and teamwork skills to coordinate the many personalities and skillsets of the team.  {&1310}\par Consultant:{&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Working as a consultant or analyst can allow you to develop a deep skillset in a particular field, or alternately, give you the flexibility to try {&1310}\par {&1310}\par Jobs:{&1310}\par CEO{&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl0\slmult1 Entrepreneur{&1310}\par Consultant{&1310}\par \pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 {&1310}\par \pard\sl0\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\f1 {&1310}\par }{&1310}
